{{Infobox football biography | name = Gevaro Nepomuceno | image = | caption = | fullname = Gevaro Nepomuceno | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1992|11|10|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Willemstad]], [[Curaçao]] | height = {{height|m=1.75}} | position = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]] | currentclub = [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] | clubnumber = 27 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = NOAD | youthyears2 = | youthclubs2 = [[RKC Waalwijk]] | youthyears3 = | youthclubs3 = [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]] | youthyears4 = | youthclubs4 = [[FC Den Bosch]] | years1 = 2011–2012 | clubs1 = [[FC Den Bosch]] | caps1 = 15 | goals1 = 1 | years2 = 2012–2014 | clubs2 = [[Fortuna Sittard]] | caps2 = 55 | goals2 = 7 | years3 = 2014–2015 | clubs3 = [[FC Petrolul Ploiești|Petrolul Ploiești]] | caps3 = 47 | goals3 = 2 | years4 = 2016–2017 | clubs4 = [[CS Marítimo|Marítimo]] | caps4 = 12 | goals4 = 0 | years5 = 2017 | clubs5 = → [[F.C. Famalicão|Famalicão]] (loan) | caps5 = 13 | goals5 = 0 | years6 = 2017– | clubs6 = [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C|Oldham Athletic]] | caps6 = 26 | goals6 = 1 | nationalyears1 = 2014– | nationalteam1 = [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao]] | nationalcaps1 = 36 | nationalgoals1 = 8 | pcupdate = 15:10, 22 September 2017 (UTC) | ntupdate = 19 November 2018 }}
'''Gevaro Nepomuceno''' (born 10 November 1992) is a [[Curaçao]]an professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Oldham Athletic]] and the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]], as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]].
==Club career== Born in [[Willemstad]], [[Curaçao]] and raised in the Netherlands, Nepomuceno started playing football when he was 12 years old, with his friends. In the next two years, it became "something important", as he said.<ref name="sportnews.ro_interview">{{cite news|url=http://www.sportnews.ro/video-l-lupul-nepomuceno-are-un-dinte-de-aur-de-la-opt-ani-6232.html|title=Gevaro Nepomuceno interview|trans-title=|date=21 May 2014|accessdate=|work=SportNews.ro|language=Romanian}}</ref> After playing for multiple clubs in the Netherlands, Nepomuceno joined Romanian side [[FC Petrolul Ploiești|Petrolul Ploiești]] during the summer of 2014, at the age of 21.<ref name="petrolul_pre-contract">{{cite news|url=http://www.fcpetrolul.ro/ro/Petrolul-i-a-transferat-pe-NKoyi-si-Nepomuceno/|title=Petrolul i-a transferat pe N’Koyi și Nepomuceno|trans-title=Petrolul transferred N'Koyi and Nepomuceno|date=6 February 2014|accessdate=|work=[[FC Petrolul Ploiești|Petrolul Ploiești]]|language=Romanian|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221171903/http://www.fcpetrolul.ro/ro/Petrolul-i-a-transferat-pe-NKoyi-si-Nepomuceno/|archivedate=21 February 2014|df=}}</ref> The manager who brought him, [[Cosmin Contra]], revealed that they were initially scouting [[Patrick N'Koyi]], the centre forward who was also transferred by Petrolul from the same team, [[Fortuna Sittard]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.digisport.ro/Sport/FOTBAL/Competitii/Europa+League/VIDEO+Cum+a+ajuns+Nepomunceno+la+Petrolul+|title=Nepomuceno a ajuns la Petrolul întâmplător: "Uită-te la băiatul ăsta, are calități extraordinare!"|trans-title=Look at this boy, he has amazing skills!|date=17 July 2014|accessdate=|work=[[DigiSport]]|language=Romanian}}</ref> He made his debut in a [[2014–15 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round|UEFA Europa League qualifying phase match]] against [[Flamurtari Vlorë]] of [[Albania]], also scoring for an eventual 2–0 win at home.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.digisport.ro/Sport/FOTBAL/Competitii/Europa+League/VIDEO+Omul+decisiv+cu+Flamurtari+Nepomuceno+a+inscris+la+debut|title=Decisiv cu Flamurtari! Nepomuceno, adus gratis din Olanda, a înscris la debut|trans-title=Decisive against Flamurtari! Nepomuceno, brought for free from the Netherlands, scored on debut|date=17 July 2014|accessdate=|work=[[DigiSport]]|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 9 April 2015, in the [[Liga I|Romanian League]], Nepomuceno netted a late winning goal against defending champions [[FC Steaua București|Steaua București]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.digisport.ro/Sport/FOTBAL/Competitii/Liga+1/VIDEO+Nepomuceno+a+adus+victoria+Petrolului+cu+primul+sau+gol+in|title=Nepomuceno a adus victoria Petrolului cu prima sa reușită în Liga 1. "Totul se va schimba acum"|trans-title=Nepomuceno brought Petrolul's victory with his first Liga 1 goal. "Everything will be different from now"|date=9 April 2015|accessdate=|work=[[DigiSport]]|language=Romanian}}</ref>
On 5 September 2017, Nepomuceno signed a one-year contract, with an option for a further year, with [[EFL League One|League One]] side [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.oldhamathletic.co.uk/news/2017/september/05092017-gevaro-nepomuceno-signs/|title=SIGNING: Winger Signs For Latics|access-date=2017-09-06|language=en-gb}}</ref>
==International career== In September 2014, Nepomuceno was called up for the first time to the senior [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçaoan national team]], to take part at the [[2014 Caribbean Cup qualification|Caribbean Cup qualification campaign]]. He scored his first goal on the 5th, against [[Grenada national football team|Grenada]]. Curaçao won the match 2–1.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cfufootball.org/index.php/caribbean-cup/9497-mens-caribbean-cup-results-sept-6|title=Men's Caribbean Cup Results Sept 6|date=6 September 2014|accessdate=|work=[[Caribbean Football Union]]}}</ref> On 13 November, Nepomuceno scored against [[Cuba national football team|Cuba]], but his team lost 2–3 and eventually failed to progress to the [[2014 Caribbean Cup#Final stage|final stage]] of the Caribbean Cup.
