{{Infobox stadium | name = Stade Ange Casanova | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = Stade Ange-Casanova.jpg | image_size = 250px | caption = Exterior of the stadium | fullname = | former_names = Stade Mezzavia | location = [[Ajaccio]], [[Corsica]], [[France]] | coordinates = {{Coord|41|57|5|N|8|46|20|E|type:landmark_region:FR|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1961 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = grass | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 8,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = [[Gazélec Football Club Olympique Ajaccio]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }}
'''Stade Ange Casanova''' is a [[Soccer-specific stadium|football stadium]] in [[Ajaccio]], [[Corsica]], [[France]] and is the home stadium of [[Gazélec Football Club Olympique Ajaccio]]. Its capacity is 8,000 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldstadiums.com/europe/countries/france/corse.shtml |title=Stadiums in France Corsica|publisher=Worldstadiums.com|accessdate=7 November 2011}}</ref>
'''Stade Mezzavia''' was built in 1961. It was renamed Stade Ange Casanova on 16 July 1994 in memory of Ange Casanova, ex-director of Gazélec. Before 1961, the club played at the Stade Miniconi.
